Let an array a have a violation at index i if it fails the target sorted condition. To transform a sequence of positive integers into a strictly ascending sequence using range multiplications:
In a Positive Segment, the number of operations required is the count of indices where a[i]>=a[i-1]
In a Negative Segment, the number of operations required is the count of indices where a[i]<=a[i-1]
